---
import Icon from '../components/common/Icon.astro';
import MarketingLayout from '../layouts/MarketingLayout.astro';
import { site } from '../data/site';

export const prerender = true;
---

<MarketingLayout
	title="About"
	description="Why Wix CLI Bible exists and what it's trying to do."
	canonicalPath="/about/"
>
	<section class="page-hero">
		<p class="eyebrow">About</p>
		<h1>I Kept Getting Lost in the Wix CLI Docs. So I Wrote Better Ones.</h1>
		<p>
			The Wix CLI is genuinely powerful. But when I was learning it, the official docs felt scattered -- concepts spread across pages, old and new CLI generations mixed together, and no clear reading order. This Open-Source project is my attempt to fix that for everyone else.
		</p>
	</section>

	<section class="section">
		<div class="story-surface" data-reveal="card">
			<div class="story-surface__copy">
				<p class="eyebrow">What This Is</p>
				<h2>A Companion to the Official Docs, Not a Replacement.</h2>
				<p>
					Wix is the source of truth for platform behavior. This handbook reorganizes that information into a learning path that makes more sense when you're starting from scratch -- structured docs, practical guides, and an AI assistant that cites its sources.
				</p>
			</div>
			<div class="story-surface__grid">
				<article class="callout-card">
					<div class="feature-icon">
						<Icon name="bookOpen" size="0.9rem" />
					</div>
					<h3>Structured Docs</h3>
					<p>16 pages in a deliberate order. Start with the mental model, then surfaces, then workflow.</p>
				</article>
				<article class="callout-card">
					<div class="feature-icon">
						<Icon name="terminal" size="0.9rem" />
					</div>
					<h3>Practical Guides</h3>
					<p>Step-by-step walkthroughs for the problems that actually come up when you're building.</p>
				</article>
				<article class="callout-card">
					<div class="feature-icon">
						<Icon name="users" size="0.9rem" />
					</div>
					<h3>Open to Contributions</h3>
					<p>Found a gap in the docs? Figured something out the hard way? You can add it here.</p>
				</article>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="section">
		<div class="story-surface" data-reveal="card">
			<div class="story-surface__copy">
				<p class="eyebrow">What We Clarify</p>
				<h2>Things the Official Docs Leave Ambiguous.</h2>
				<p>
					We're not here to criticize the Wix team -- they built the platform. But some things in the official docs are genuinely confusing, and we try to clarify them here so developers don't waste time.
				</p>
			</div>
			<div class="story-surface__grid">
				<article class="callout-card">
					<div class="feature-icon">
						<Icon name="alertTriangle" size="0.9rem" />
					</div>
					<h3>Three CLIs, One Name</h3>
					<p>The unified CLI, legacy CLI for Apps, and CLI for Sites all exist under "Wix CLI." We map which is which so you don't read the wrong docs.</p>
				</article>
				<article class="callout-card">
					<div class="feature-icon">
						<Icon name="alertTriangle" size="0.9rem" />
					</div>
					<h3>Preview vs Release</h3>
					<p>The official docs mention this, but it's easy to miss. Some extensions don't work until you release -- not just preview. We make that prominent.</p>
				</article>
				<article class="callout-card">
					<div class="feature-icon">
						<Icon name="alertTriangle" size="0.9rem" />
					</div>
					<h3>Registry File Naming</h3>
					<p>The official project structure diagram shows "extension.ts" but the actual file is "extensions.ts" (plural). Small typo, real confusion.</p>
				</article>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="section">
		<div class="support-surface support-surface--compact" data-reveal="card">
			<div class="support-surface__copy">
				<span class="pill">
					<Icon name="gitBranch" size="0.85rem" />
					Moenga Space
				</span>
				<h2>Built by Moenga Space. Open-Source for Everyone.</h2>
				<p>This is a side project built because the need was real. Contributions, feedback, and corrections are always welcome.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="support-surface__actions">
				<a class="button" href={site.repoUrl} target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">
					<Icon name="githubLogo" size="0.85rem" />
					View Source
				</a>
				<a class="button-secondary" href="/guides/contributing-a-guide/">
					<Icon name="arrowRight" size="0.85rem" />
					Contribute
				</a>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>
</MarketingLayout>
